        "text_AcHkT6": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Picture this. It's 11 AM in Delhi. The temperature is already 44°C. You're standing at a DTC bus stop, shirt already soaked through. Your phone battery is at 18%. And you've still got 8 hours ahead of you.</p><p>You've tried the neck fan — the buzz is embarrassing and the breeze barely reaches your face. Handheld fans mean one hand always occupied. Table fans stop working the moment the power goes. And AC? — <em>Only works when you're sitting still indoors.</em></p><p>What if staying cool wasn't a luxury — <strong>but a ₹2,499 clip on your waistband?</strong></p>",
            "text_size": 16,
            "text_color": "#1d1d1d",
            "highlighted_text_color": "#000000",
            "highlighted_text_background": "#fcc947",
            "accent_text_color": "#2563eb",
